          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SOLST",
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two solid-state counter telescopes",
                "were used in the chamber, mounted on two rotatable arms",
                "accurately centred about the target position."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The stopping counters were 1.5 mm thick silicon",
                "surface-barrier detectors preceded by 0.1 mm",
                "silicon surface-barrier passing counters providing",
                "discrimination of deuterons against other types of",
                "particles produced in reactions.",
                "The deuteron beam polarization was monitored",
                "continuously in a carbon polarimeter measuring the",
                "asymmetry in the elastic scattering of deuterons by",
                "A 6.7 mg/cm2 thick self-supporting carbon target was",
                "used in the polarimeter and deuterons scattered",
                "elasticly to the left and to the right by 25. degr.",
                "were detected in two silicon surface-barrier detectors,",
                "each accepted +-3 degr."
              ]
            }
          ],
